HEADWORD: Portulacaceous
<hw>Por`tu*la*ca"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to a natural order of plants
(<ord>Portulacace⟦ae⟧</ord>), of which Portulaca is the type, and which
includes also the spring beauty (<gen>Claytonia</gen>) and other
genera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

